When the idea was introduced in Ireland it was adopted in the towns and cities, but not everywhere by farming communities.  In the rural district in which I lived the newly-introduced summer time  was called &quot;New Time&quot; but we had &quot;Old Time&quot; all year round. We had to be careful when planning to attend an event elsewhere; was it  &quot;New Time&quot; or &quot;Old Time&quot;
